          "passage": "Linguist Deborah Tannen has cautioned against framing contentious issues in terms of two highly competitive perspectives, such as pro versus\ncon. According to Tannen, this debate-driven approach can strip issues of their complexity and, when used in front of an audience, can be less\ninformative than the presentation of multiple perspectives in a noncompetitive format. To test Tannen ’ s hypothesis, students conducted a study\nin which they showed participants one of three diff erent versions of local news commentary about the same issue. Each version featured a\ndebate between two commentators with opposing views, a panel of three commentators with various views, or a single commentator.",
