          "passage": "In their book Smart Pricing, Jagmohan Raju and Z. John Zhang consider musicians’ use of the nontraditional “ pay as you wish ” pricing model.\nThis model generally offers listeners the choice to pay more or less than a suggested price for a song or album—or even to pay nothing at all. As\nthe authors note, that’ s the option most listeners chose for an album by the band Harvey Danger. Only about 1% opted to pay for the album,\nresulting in earnings below the band’ s expectations. But the authors also discuss musician Jane Siberry, who saw significant earnings from her\n“ pay as you wish ” online music store as a result of many listeners choosing to pay more than the store ’ s suggested prices. Hence, the “ pay as you\nwish ” model may ______",
