          "passage": "When fashion designer Lloyd Henri Kiva New opened his store in Scottsdale, Arizona, in 1945, he quickly became known for creating delicately\ncrafted leather goods, like belts and hats. He was perhaps most renowned for his colorful handbags, which he made by hand using a long and\npainstaking process. As he gained more customers, New began using sewing machines and other tools to help him produce bags more\nefficiently, though he continued to handcraft the crucial details that made each bag unique.",
