          "category": "Central Ideas and Details",
          "questionType": "Central Ideas and Details",
          "difficulty": "Easy",
          "passage": "The following text is adapted from Johanna Spyri’s 1881 novel Heidi (translated by Elisabeth Stork in 1915). Eight-year-old Heidi and her friend’s\ngrandmother are looking at some illustrated books.\nHeidi had come and was looking with wondering eyes at the splendid pictures in the large books, that Grandmama was showing\nher. Suddenly she screamed aloud, for there on the picture she saw a peaceful flock grazing on a green pasture. In the middle a\nshepherd was standing, leaning on his crook. The setting sun was shedding a golden light over everything. With glowing eyes\nHeidi devoured the scene.",
          "question": "Which choice best states the main idea of the text?",
