          "passage": "Many of William Shakespeare’s tragedies address broad themes that still appeal to today’s audiences. For instance, Romeo and Juliet, which is\nset in the Italy of Shakespeare’s time, tackles the themes of parents versus childr en and love versus hate, and the play continues to be read and\nproduced widely around the world. But understanding Shakespeare’s so-called history plays can require a knowledge of several centuries of\nEnglish history. Consequently, ______",
