          "passage": "Data Sources for Neptune Temperature Analysis\nObservatory Data type Observation years\nGemini Observatory spectroscopy 2007, 2019\nT-ReCS (Thermal-Region Camera Spectrograph) Gemini Observatory infrared imaging 2007, 2010\nLWS (Long Wavelength Spectrometer) Keck Observatory infrared imaging 2003\nVISIR (VLT Imager and Spectrometer for mid-InfraRed) European Southern Observatory spectroscopy 2006\nInstrument TEXES (Texas Echelon Cross Echelle Spectrograph) Julianne I. Moses and colleagues have reported that Neptune may have cooled significantly between 2003 and 2020. The team reached this\nconclusion by analyzing existing infrared imaging and spectroscopy data about the planet obtained from various instruments in different years.\nOf the team’s sources listed in the table, the earliest example of spectroscopy data included in the analysis was obtained in ______",
