          "passage": "Biologist Valentina Gómez-Bahamón and her team have investigated two subspecies of the fork-tailed flycatcher bird that live in the same region\nin Colombia, but one subspecies migrates south for part of the year, and the other doesn’t. The researchers found that, due to slight differ ences\nin feather shape, the feathers of migratory forked-tailed flycatcher males make a sound during flight that is higher pitched than that made by the\nfeathers of nonmigratory males. The researchers hypothesize that fork-tailed flycatcher females are attracted to the specific sound made by the\nmales of their own subspecies, and that over time the females’preference will drive further genetic and anatomical divergence between the\nsubspecies.",
