          "difficulty": "Medium",
          "passage": "E-book Sales as a Percentage of Total Unit Sales in All Book\nFormats for a Large US Trade Publisher, by Genre, 2006,\n2011, 2016\nGenre 2006 2011 2016\nscience fiction and fantasy 0.6 27.7 36.7\ncookbooks 0 2.9 10.5\ntravel guides 0 5.5 24.6\nromance 0.3 40.6 56.2\nE-books became an increasingly popular means of reading in the United States in the 2000s and 2010s, though that popularity was concentrated\nin titles that, like those in most fiction genres, are meant to be read straight through from beginning to end. For books in nonfiction genres that\ndo not tell stories and require the reader to flip back and for th through a volume, e-books were significantly less commercially successful. This\ncan be seen by comparing ______",
