          "passage": "The Nacional tree is a rare variety of cacao. Nacionals were thought to have gone extinct by the twentieth century due to a fungus. This fungus\ncan spread from tree to nearby tree through the air and causes disease. But around 2013, cacao exper t Servio Pachard located some of these\nNacional trees. The trees were in the Piedra de Plata coastal forest, within a hard-to-reach valley in Ecuador. Conservationists inferred that the\nNacional trees in Piedra de Plata might have avoided the diseases that wiped out the other Nacionals because ______",
