          "passage": "The following text is from Mark Haber’s 2022 novel Saint Sebastian’s Abyss. The narrator and Schmidt are both art critics.\nWhen my first wife admitted to Schmidt over dinner that she didn’t find art, painting in particular, especially compelling, Schmidt\nwinced, set down his fork, and sighed dramatically; he then excused himself, explaining an appointment he’d forgotten about had\nsuddenly and inexplicably been remembered, while making it abundantly clearthere was no appointment at all.\n©2022 by Mark Haber",
