          "questionType": "Command of Evidence",
          "difficulty": "Hard",
          "passage": "Ar t collectives, like the United States- and Vietnam-based collective The Propeller Group or Cuba’s Los Carpinteros, are groups of artists who\nagree to work together: perhaps for stylistic reasons, or to advance certain shared political ideals, or to help mitigate the costs of supplies and\nstudio space. Regardless of the reasons, art collectives usually involve some collaboration among the artists. Based on a recent series of\ninterviews with various art collectives, an arts journalist claims that this can be difficult for artists who are often used to having sole control over\ntheir work.",
