          "passage": "Born in 1891 to a Quechua-speaking family in the Andes Mountains of Peru, Mart n Chambi is today considered to be one of the most renowned\nfigures of Latin American photography. In a paper for an art history class, a student claims that Chambi’s photographs have considerable\nethnographic value—in his work, Chambi was able to capture diverse elements of Peruvian society, representing his subjects with both dignity\nand authenticity.",
