          "passage": "Correlations Between Congestion Ratings and Features of\nthe Crowd in Raters’Immediate Vicinity\nCrowd feature Before obstacle After obstacle Overall\nDensity 0.8592 0.7308 0.7447\nVelocity −0.9357 −0.9518 −0.8587\nResearcher Xiaolu Jia and colleagues monitored individuals’velocity and the surrounding crowd density as a gr oup of study participants walked\nthrough a space and navigated around an obstacle. Participants rated how congested it seemed before the obstacle, after the obstacle, and\noverall, and the researchers correlated those ratings with velocity and density. (Correlations range from −1 to 1, with greater distance from 0\nindicating greater strength). The researchers concluded that the correlations with velocity are stronger than those with density.",
