          "category": "Inferences",
          "questionType": "Inferences",
          "difficulty": "Easy",
          "passage": "To create the poems in her 2017 collection One Last Word, poet Nikki Grimes used a writing method called the golden shovel. This method often\ninvolves choosing a line from an existing poem and then using each word from that line as the last wor d of each line in a new poem. Grimes\nwanted the poems in One Last Word to honor important Black poets of the past, so she chose lines by poets such as Langston Hughes and\nGeorgia Douglas Johnson. Writing in this way can be challenging and might seem as though it would produce awkward poems. However,\nreviewers praised One Last Word as a beautiful and powerful tribute to the poets who inspired it. This reaction suggests that ______",
          "question": "Which choice most logically completes the text?",
